    <string name="how_to_use_title">How to use?</string>
    <string name="how_to_use_content">1. Enable the engines you need in Settings (⚙️).\n2. Link the Main Engine folder (the one containing \'mods\' or \'modList.txt\').\n3. After reinstalling, you must link again due to Android security.</string>

    <string name="installation_guide_title">Installation Guide</string>

    <string name="guide_scoped_title">Scoped Storage Installation</string>
    <string name="guide_scoped_content">If it is scoped/data, you will have to give access to the root folder of the data of the respective game where you will install the mods, it can/should be */files/*; if you gave consent, then it is already correctly linked to the folder.</string>

    <string name="guide_external_title">External Storage Installation</string>
    <string name="guide_external_content">If it is external, you will have to give access to the root folder of the engine name, it usually comes after a dot \".PsychEngine\" and so on, to that folder you must give access to the app; like the previous one, if you gave the folder consents correctly, then it is already correctly linked to the folder.</string>

    <string name="guide_funkin_mobile_title">Funkin Mobile Mods</string>
    <string name="guide_funkin_mobile_content">For Funkin Mobile, the new function to disable mods was added, basically this will move the mods you have inside /mods/ to a folder accompanied by it called /mods_disabled/ and you can normally switch between enabling and disabling.</string>

    <string name="guide_engines_title">Engines Mods</string>
    <string name="guide_engines_content">For Engines, these will normally be taken from modList.txt</string>

    <string name="guide_unlinking_title">Why folders get unlinked?</string>
    <string name="guide_unlinking_content">Android may revoke folder permissions after an app update, system restart, or if the app cache is cleared. If this happens, just press \"Link Now\" again to restore access.</string>

